Wait what's up?
So essentially you have a separate project for each functional component so they're completely in isolated from each other and deployed/built independently
i.e. Booking is one project, Auth would be another, Account would also be a different one which included all account related functionality such as update information such as security and creating an account
Anything with Booking should be its own solution
So from what I understand @Giorady has two projects since he's working on two components/microservices and @Thanh you have one since it's one area
Does that make sense?
It's not isolated based on functionality per say but it's isolated by business areas/domain (edited)
The login process is separate from anything account related and so is the booking separated from all of that (edited)
If booking had 10 functions i.e. create, list, update, compare x to y, etc it's still one project
